    VP, Exhibitor Services, Sales and Business Development, International CES</p>
    <hr align="center" width="90%" size="1" noshade color="#999999">
    <!-- article start -->
    <p>
    <strong>Media at CES: Your “Pro-Bono” Promotional Partner</strong><br> by Dan Cole</p>
    <p>Continued from <a href="/print/exhibitors/newsletter/oct08.asp">first page</a>.</p>
    <SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #3a3a3a; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">This media monsoon has led to the CES keynotes being ranked among the top 10 desired speaking opportunities for CEO’s by PR firm Burson-Marstellar. But media coverage opportunities aren’t limited to the large multi-national companies that participate in CES. If you need to get your products and technology in front of the media, CES is the must attend event for you. The CES media season kicks off on November 11 at the New York Press Preview, at the Metropolitan Pavilion, in New York City. Held in conjunction with the CES Unveiled, this event offers press an insider view of the products that will both turn heads for the upcoming holiday season and make waves in January at CES. The media buzz then continues on January 6th at CES Unveiled in Las Vegas, the official press event of International CES. Here, over 700 press come to get a sneak peak of what will be debuting on the CES show floor that week. </SPAN></SPAN>

<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">If you have major company or product news to announce, you are also more than welcome to secure a press conference slot during the show. </SPAN></SPAN></P>

<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">At CES, the press can serve as your pro-bono advertising agency, and no other technology event offers more access. <BR></SPAN></P></SPAN>
    <!-- article end -->
    <img src="/print/images/content/dan_cole_sig.gif"><br>Dan Cole
