<a name="2099"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Don't Miss Your Chance to be a Guest on &quot;Into Tomorrow with Dave Graveline&quot; -- THE Consumer Electronics Radio Show! </div>
<br />

<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><IMG height=152 hspace=10 src="/print/images/content/graveline.jpg" width=159 align=right>Dave and his team will once again be broadcasting from the upcoming CES as they launch their 14th season covering the latest in CE products -- including producing their national show from the CES Unveiled New York event on November 11, CES Unveiled in Las Vegas on January 6 and the 2009 International CES in January from January 8-11. If you will be introducing new and exciting consumer electronics products or services and would like to be considered as a guest, contact Dave's Producer, Rob Almanza ASAP via rob@graveline.com. Dave's team will also be producing "Video Booth Tours" during CES week as well as offering additional promotional opportunities during their broadcasts. </SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">More info at <A title=http://www.graveline.com/ href="http://www.graveline.com/" target=_blank>http://www.graveline.com/</A>. </SPAN></P>

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2098"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Submissions Are Now Open for Best of CES Awards 2009!</div>
<br />

<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><IMG height=115 hspace=10 src="/print/images/content/CNET.jpg" width=60 align=right>Presented by CNET, these esteemed awards recognize the best new products at the show. Winning products are selected by CNET’s expert editors, so grab their attention before the show by submitting today! For more information, visit the <A title=http://www.cnet.com/best-of-ceshttp://www.cnet.com/4520-13403_1-6722486-1.html href="http://www.cnet.com/best-of-ces" target=_blank>Awards We Give page</A> at <A href="http://www.cnet.com/about" target=_blank>CNET.com/about</A>.</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2097"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Deliver Your Message on The CE Channel </div>
<br />

<P><SPAN class=text1><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><IMG height=93 hspace=10 src="/print/images/content/CE_Channel(1).jpg" width=90 align=right vspace=10>Use the power of TV to reach CES attendees with your sales and marketing message, to make product announcements, and drive booth traffic. The CE Channel™ airs around the clock in 75,000 Las Vegas hotel rooms during CES. Viewers will see reports from the floor, highlights of the keynotes, interviews with executives, and insights from analysts and journalists. As a sponsor, you will be seen and heard by this targeted audience. For more about this unique and cost-effective opportunity, go to <A href="http://www.thecechannel.tv/" target=_blank>http://www.thecechannel.tv/</A> or call 413-623-2221.</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></SPAN></P>

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2096"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Reach Tech-Savvy CE Industry Movers by Advertising in Official Show Publications </div>
<br />

<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><IMG height=24 hspace=10 src="/print/images/content/CTPG_logo.gif" width=150 align=right vspace=10>The Consumer Technology Publishing Group (CTPG) of North American Publishing Co. is the custom publisher of the official <I>Preshow Planner, Show Guide</I> and <I>Directory</I> for the International CES. <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/sponsorships/printAdvertising.asp#741" target=_blank>Visit the CES promotional opportunities page for full details.</A></SPAN></P>

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2061"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Explore Marketing Options on CES Daily Microsite Produced by TWICE </div>
<br />
<IMG height=41 hspace=10 src="/print/images/content/twice.gif" width=150 align=right>The CES Daily Microsite featuring accurate, timely news and products -- helping to put the show into perspective -- is presented by TWICE, publisher of the official daily of CES. With heavy promotion to show-goers, the site will be a must-read, making it a must-advertise-in opportunity.
<P>Call for CES packages: 646-746-6980; <A href="mailto:aloma.arter@reedbusiness.com" target=_blank>aloma.arter@reedbusiness.com</A>.<BR></P>

        <img width="1" height="30" src="/print/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/print/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2060"></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Exclusive CEA Member Benefits at 2009 International CES </div>
<br />
<IMG height=53 hspace=10 src="/print/images/content/CEA.gif" width=150 align=right>CEA Members receive exclusive benefits whether attending or exhibiting at the International CES. Exhibitors who join CEA by December 19 will be eligible to receive various discounts and perks, such as member priority for 2010 CES space selection, a free parking pass and VIP luncheon tickets. CEA member exhibitors and attendees are also invited to access member lounges with private meeting rooms, e-mail work stations, and refreshments. 
<P>Get more information or apply online, or contact <A href="mailto: jbiggs@ce.org" target=_blank>Jennifer Biggs</A> at 703-907-7756. <BR></P>

